  "text": "DCs may also enter injured kidneys from the peripheral blood, have a short half-life and are most often located within interstitial lymphoid infiltrates [CITATION_1] . We confirmed that pDCs, myeloid DCs and CLEC9A + DCs are all present in the kidneys of LN patients. Renal infiltration of these classic DC cell types is associated with the later stages of renal injury and fibrosis in human glomerular diseases [CITATION_2] .",
